---
title: "Codio for Universities"
fixed: true
---
<% @pricingType = "university" %>
<% @signupUrl = "/p/free-education-trial" %>

<section class='header-block'>
  <h1 class="animated fadeIn">
    The easier, smarter way
    to teach coding
  </h1>
  <h2>
    Code anywhere, flexible and hassle-free, puts you in charge of course
    content, and significant savings too.
  </h2>
  <div class="action-buttons animated fadeInUp">
    <%= link_to 'Start FREE Trial', '/p/free-education-trial', class: 'button button-xlarge button-main' %>
    <%= link_to 'Book a Demo', '/demo', class: 'button button-xlarge button-main button-demo' %>
  </div>
  <div class="clear">
  </div>
</section>

<section class="university-body">
  <div class="section top">
    <h4 class="section-header">Codio For Universities and Colleges</h4>

    <div class="section-block-row">
      <div class="section-block">
        <div class="section-block-copy">
          Codio is built for computer science educators, and contains a unique
          combination of technologies that you’ll find hard to match. Codio
          provides an entire infrastructure stack in the cloud to give your
          students access to their code projects at any time.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-block">
        <div class="section-block-copy">
          And it offers you great visibility too — with tools that let you
          monitor progress and provide support and feedback. Plus, you can
          easily author new course content or adapt Codio’s stacks to create
          your own learning templates.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section first">
    <h3 class="section-header">
      Infographics
    </h3>
    <div class="section-body">

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="blue">
    <div class="section second">
      <div class="section-block-column">
        <div class="section-block">
          <div class="border-wrapper">
            <%= inline_svg "assets/university/layers.svg", class: "icon white" %>
          </div>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Templates for your students
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            Project setup can be a serious pain. Codio lets you
            configure a template machine with all the software
            configuration and code you need, then publish it for students to
            use instantly.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section-block">
          <div class="border-wrapper">
            <%= inline_svg "assets/university/atom.svg", class: "icon white" %>
          </div>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Conflict free
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            Working with multiple projects and software environments often creates version
            control and software configuration issues. Because all Codio projects
            have their own dedicated server, there is no risk of conflicting components.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="wow fadeIn" data-wow-duration=".8s" data-wow-delay="1s">
        <%= image_tag 'assets/university/console.png', class: "right-image" %>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section third">
    <div class="border-wrapper headline">
      <%= inline_svg "assets/university/ekg.svg", class: "icon" %>
    </div>

    <h3 class="section-header">
      Student management tools
    </h3>
    <div class="section-body">

      <div class="section-block-row">
        <div class="section-block">
          <%= inline_svg "assets/university/tools.svg", class: "icon" %>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Class management
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            Codio offers full support for managing classes and assigning projects or
            course content. Creating class groups and sharing course resources is easy -
            and our dashboard allows you to track student engagement.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section-block">
          <%= inline_svg "assets/university/code.svg", class: "icon" %>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Immediate access to students' code
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            You can instantly access and execute students' code.
            You'll have the matching stack as you're accessing the student's server
            and configuration directly. As a result, there's no code sharing by email or USB drive.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="blue">
    <div class="section fourth">
      <div class="section-block-column">
        <div class="section-block">
          <div class="border-wrapper">
            <%= inline_svg "assets/university/pencil.svg", class: "icon white" %>
          </div>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Content authoring
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            Codio's editor lets you create your own course content that is tightly bound to the IDE.
            Tutorial pages can control the IDE, open files, command lines or previews.
            Students can interact with and modify live code, creating a uniquely different learning experience.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section-block">
          <div class="border-wrapper">
            <%= inline_svg "assets/university/math.svg", class: "icon white" %>
          </div>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Integrated assessments
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            Teachers can embed several different assessment types in their tutorials,
            including automated code tests, MCQs, the ability to grade code and more.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section-block">
          <div class="border-wrapper">
            <%= inline_svg "assets/university/folders.svg", class: "icon white" %>
          </div>
          <h4 class="section-block-header">
            Codio courses
          </h4>
          <div class="section-block-copy">
            Codio courses are an ideal foundation in the areas of general programming,
            Web Development, MySQL, Linux and standard search and sort algorithms.
            Courses contain auto-graded assessments that provide
            instant teacher feedback via the class dashboards.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="wow fadeIn" data-wow-duration=".8s" data-wow-delay="1s">
        <%= image_tag 'assets/university/guide.png', class: "right-image" %>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%= partial "call-to-action", locals: { url: "/p/free-education-trial", pricing: "university" } %>
</section>
